<div class="box en">💡 <strong>What to watch now:</strong> $1.43 billion in BTC/ETH options expired on July 17. BTC's $63,000 max pain nearly matched the actual spot price of $63,394. Watch (1) whether the BTC-call/ETH-put decoupling (put-call ratios of 0.9 and 1.61) persists into the next expiry, (2) whether the rising bullish block trades convert into real spot buying, and (3) whether the next monthly/quarterly expiry brings a larger notional value than this one.</div>
